HEADWORD: Ditrichotomous
<hw>Di`tri*chot"o*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>trichotomous</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Divided into twos or threes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Dividing into double or treble
ramifications; -- said of a leaf or stem.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Loudon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ditrochean</ent>⟦br⟧
